%S A395026 0,0,0,0,1,1,10,50,316,1809,10549,60335,344504,1956846,11098060,
%T A395026 62859314
%N A395026 a(n) is the number of polyominoes in the hyperbolic regular tiling with Schläfli symbol {4,5} requiring 3 colors so that no 2 adjacent cells have the same color.
%C A395026 Any {4,4} polyomino (i.e., Euclidean) is 2-colorable. Conversely, some {4,5} polyominoes require 3 colors (see example in links). On the other hand, by Grötzsch's theorem, no such polyomino requires more than 3 colors.
%C A395026 This sequence was calculated in the context of a project in collaboration with Érika Roldán, and Rosemberg Toalá-Enríquez.
%H A395026 John Mason, <a href="/A395026/a395026_1.png">Example polyomino requiring 3 colors</a>
%H A395026 Wikipedia, <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Order-5_square_tiling">Order-5_square_tiling</a>
%e A395026 a(5) = 1 because of the {4,5} polyomino having 5 cells with a common vertex.
%Y A395026 Cf. A119611.
%K A395026 nonn,more,new
%O A395026 1,7
